      "message": "[warning] Line 52: The `status` property now carries two different semantic domains in the same expression: raw contact-presence codes (0/1/2) and `Account.Status` enum values. Because the contact-presence branch (`status \u003d\u003d\u003d 1 || status \u003d\u003d\u003d 2`) is evaluated *before* the `Account.Status` branches, any `Account.Status` enum member whose integer value is 1 or 2 will be silently mis-colored green. This depends on an undocumented, fragile assumption about the enum\u0027s numeric layout (e.g. that TRYING/UNREGISTERED are \u003e\u003d 3). Please (a) confirm no `Account.Status` value collides with 0/1/2, and (b) replace the magic numbers with named constants / an enum (e.g. an explicit contact-presence enum) so the two domains cannot overlap and the intent is self-documenting.",
